definitions.definition: The soft skin on each side of the face, below the eyes; the outer surface of the sides of the oral cavity.
The lower part of the buttocks that is often exposed beneath very brief underwear , swimwear , or extremely short shorts .
definitions.label_groups: anatomy , informal , usually in the plural

examples: You’ve got some cheek , asking me for money!

definitions.definition: One of the genae , flat areas on the sides of a trilobite 's cephalon .
One of the pieces of a machine , or of timber or stonework , that form corresponding sides or a similar pair.
examples: the cheeks of a gun carriage

subdefinitions.definition: pump -cheek, pump -cheeks, a piece of wood cut out fork-shaped in which the brake is fastened by means of a bolt and can thus move around and move the upper box of the pump up and down

definitions.definition: The branches of a bridle bit .
The middle section of a flask , made so that it can be moved laterally, to permit the removal of the pattern from the mould.
